    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="116"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Baron <persName
                            type="to">Fava</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Baron</hi>: I hasten to send for your information a
                    copy of a telegram from his excellency the governor of Colorado of to-day’s
                    date, touching the recent affair at Walsenburg, in that State.</p>
                <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="0208" n="942" xml:id="pg_942"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure—Telegram.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Governor <persName type="from">McIntire</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>
                        </hi>.</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Denver, Colo.</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-16">
                                <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1895</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>I have reliable information that two of the Italians lynched positively had
                        first and probably second citizenship papers. Not known whether Danino was
                        an American citizen. It is asserted that the two prisoners who may have
                        escaped from first attack of mob had first citizenship papers. The fate of
                        the last two not known, as they have not been heard from since their escape.
                        I have directed proper district attorney to take speedy steps looking to
                        arrest and conviction of the guilty parties in the Walsenburg affair.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Albert W. McIntire</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Governor</hi>.</signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
